cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper presents a method for generating exploration behaviors for a microfarming robot using deep neural networks and online learning. The focus is on intrinsic motivation and episodic memory to prevent catastrophic forgetting. Given the use of robotics and machine learning, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves deep neural networks, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another likely sub-category. The use of artificial curiosity and online learning further supports cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category. The exploration is based on image data, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for learning and memory suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a potential sub-category.
